Reference-contexts: The "Permutation-Equivalence Assumption" (PEA) generalizes IEA to apply to relations of arbitrary arity. 4 The Qua Relation We next consider the qua (role-as-concept) relationship <ref> [Freeman 81] </ref>. Let us define the class Employee, to be "a person who works for a company", (i.e., Employee is qua-induced by the relation companies). Fred as an instance of Person corresponds to two distinct individuals in the class Employee: Fred-as-IBM-worker and Fred-as-Apple-worker.
