Reference-contexts: The consequences of IEA percolate up to the meta level. At the meta level, conceptual objects representing classes of tuples (i.e., relations) are distinct from conceptual objects representing classes of reified tuples. To provide support for NL applications such as PENMAN <ref> [Hovy 90] </ref>, Loom implements a construct called defreified-relation which, upon invocation, defines a pair of meta objects, one denoting a binary relation, and one denoting the corresponding class of reified tuples. Let us name the class of reified companies tuples Workers/companies and name the class of reified workers tuples Companies/workers.
